"content": "<h2>Vinegar made from wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:1-Num6:4\">NUM 6:1–6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:14\">RUT 2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Vinegar as an acid, reacting vigorously with alkaline soda</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:20\">PRO 25:20</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Vinegar as a substitute for wine</h2>\n<h3>Its unpleasantness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:26\">PRO 10:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:19-Ps69:22\">PSA 69:19–69:22</a></p>\n<h3>It was offered to Jesus Christ at the crucifixion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:48-Matt27:50\">MAT 27:48–27:50</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:36-Mark15:37\">MRK 15:36–15:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:36-Luke23:37\">LUK 23:36–23:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:28-John19:30\">JHN 19:28–19:30</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:21\">PSA 69:21</a></p>",
